# âœ… Question 3 (Problem Statement)

> **Design and deploy a static website using Docker and host it on AWS EC2 instance. The website should be accessible using the public IP address of the EC2 instance.**

## ðŸŸ¢ Step 1 â€“ Install Docker on Local Machine

Check:

```bash
docker --version
```

If not installed â†’ Install Docker Desktop.

---

## ðŸŸ¢ Step 2 â€“ Create Project Folder

```bash
mkdir mywebsite
cd mywebsite
```

---

## ðŸŸ¢ Step 3 â€“ Create Static Website

Create file: `index.html`

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<title>Static Website</title>
</head>
<body>
<h1>Welcome to Docker Website</h1>
<p>Hosted on AWS EC2</p>
</body>
</html>
```

---

## ðŸŸ¢ Step 4 â€“ Create Dockerfile

Create file: `Dockerfile`

```dockerfile
FROM nginx:alpine
COPY index.html /usr/share/nginx/html/index.html
EXPOSE 80
```

---

## ðŸŸ¢ Step 5 â€“ Build Docker Image (Local)

```bash
docker build -t college-site .
```

---

## ðŸŸ¢ Step 6 â€“ Test Locally

```bash
docker run -d -p 8080:80 college-site
```

Open:

```
http://localhost:8080
```

Stop:

```bash
docker stop <container-id>
```

---

## ðŸŸ¢ Step 7 â€“ Create AWS EC2 Instance

* Ubuntu 22.04
* Instance type: t2.micro
* Open ports:

  * 22 (SSH)
  * 80 (HTTP)

---

## ðŸŸ¢ Step 8 â€“ Connect to EC2

```bash
ssh -i key.pem ubuntu@PUBLIC_IP
```

---

## ðŸŸ¢ Step 9 â€“ Install Docker on EC2

```bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt install docker.io -y
sudo systemctl start docker
sudo usermod -aG docker ubuntu
exit
```

Login again.

---

## ðŸŸ¢ Step 10 â€“ Copy Project to EC2

From local:

```bash
scp -i key.pem -r mywebsite ubuntu@PUBLIC_IP:/home/ubuntu/
```

---

## ðŸŸ¢ Step 11 â€“ Build Image on EC2

```bash
cd mywebsite
docker build -t college-site .
```

---

## ðŸŸ¢ Step 12 â€“ Run Container on EC2

```bash
docker run -d -p 80:80 --name website college-site
```

---

## ðŸŸ¢ Step 13 â€“ Access Website

Open browser:

```
http://PUBLIC_IP
```

---

# âœ… Final Result

Static website successfully hosted using Docker on AWS EC2.

